    • Constructor Detail

      • ScheduledExecutor

        public ScheduledExecutor(boolean throwable,
                         java.util.logging.Logger logger)
        Create instance that execute schedule tasks in fixed rate with result. The execution rate will happen every default time.
        Parameters:
        throwable - if true the method IStartable.Start() will throw RuntimeException on error case. if false only the IStartable state will changed.
        logger - A logger to write to it.
        See Also:
        IStartable

      • ScheduledExecutor

        public ScheduledExecutor(boolean throwable,
                         java.util.logging.Logger logger,
                         int initialDelay,
                         int executionPeriod,
                         java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit timeUnit)
        Create instance that execute schedule tasks in fixed rate with result.
        Parameters:
        throwable - if true the method IStartable.Start() will throw RuntimeException on error case. if false only the IStartable state will changed.
        logger - A logger to write to it.
        initialDelay - the time to delay first
        executionPeriod - the period between successive executions
        timeUnit - the time unit of the initialDelay and period parameters
        See Also:
        IStartable

                               java.util.concurrent.Callable<TData> callable,
                               @Nullable
                               ScheduledExecutor.IScheduledExecutionHandler<TData> executionHandle)
        Add task to the executor, if the executor is in 'Stopped' state.
        Type Parameters:
        TData - Scheduled task result type.
        Parameters:
        callable - The scheduled task - Can not be null.
        executionHandle - A handler of the scheduled task result.
        Returns:

      • toExecute

        protected boolean toExecute()
        The method called when the received period has been passed and the method check the precondition to execution of the tasks. The default implementation always returns true, it may be overridden by extending class.
        Returns:
        true to continue execution of the tasks, and false for skip the execution this time.
